    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab><persName><name ref="Ermiteus">Ermiteo</name></persName> filio
                            <persName>bone memorie <name ref="Peredeo">Peritei</name></persName>
                        permuta beni con <persName ref="#people/214" key="#Bishops"
                            >Gherardus</persName> gratia Dei huius Sancte Lucane ecclesie humilis
                            <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> (…). (…). Ermiteo cede a Gherardo ad
                        parte ecclesie <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/219">Sancti
                            Prosperi</orgName>, sita loco <placeName ref="#places/555"
                            >Interacchule</placeName>, quod est de suppotestate ipsius <rs
                            key="#Mother_churches">episcopatui</rs> vestro <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/68" key="#Mother_churches">Sancti
                            Martini</orgName>, idest quinque petiis de terris et vineis meis illis,
                        quam abeo in loco et finibus <placeName key="#Confinia" ref="#places/22"
                            >Flexo</placeName>, ubi dicitur <placeName ref="#places/3327"
                            >Faugnano</placeName> prope ecclesiam <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3318">Sancte Marie</orgName>, que una ex ipse
                        petie est tenentes uno caput in terra <orgName>Sancti Alexandri</orgName>,
                        alio caput tenet in vinea ipsius ecclesie Sancti Alexandri, lato uno tenet
                        in vinea suprascripte ecclesie Sancti Alexandri et in aliquantulo in vinea
                        Peretei diac; et illa alia petia capo uno tenet in vinea <rs
                            key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/79" key="#Confinia #Monasteries">Sancti
                            Petri de <placeName ref="#places/85" key="#Monasteries"
                                >Monteviride</placeName></orgName>, alio caput tenet in <rs
                            key="#Rivers">fluvio Ausere</rs>, lato uno tenet in via, alio lato tenet
                        in vinea qui fuit <persName>qd. <name ref="Teudemundus"
                            >Teudimundi</name></persName>; et ille tertia petia capo uno cum uno
                        lato tenet in terra suprascritpe ecclesie Sancti Alexandri, alio caput tenet
                        in via, alio tenet in terra de ff. <persName>qd. <name ref="Clifferadus"
                                >Clifferadi</name></persName>; et illa quarta petia caput uno tenet
                        in terra, qui fuit suprascripti qd. Teudimundi, alio caput cum uno lato
                        tenet in via, et alio lato tenet in terra suprascripti monasterii Sancti
                        Petri de Monteviride; et illa quinta petia capo uno cum uno lato tenet in
                        via publica, alio caput tenet in terra qui fuit <persName key="#Priests">qd.
                                <name ref="Christofalus">Cristofali</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbitero</rs>, alio lato tenet in vinea suprascripti
                        monasterii Sancti Alexandri; suprascripte quinque petiis de terris et vineis
                        (…) sunt per mensura ad iusta perticha mensuratas modiorum quattuor et
                        sist(ariorum) sex (…) cum cesis et fossis seo omnibus arboribus suis (…).
                        Riceve in cambio: quinque petiis de terris et vineis in loco et finibus
                            <placeName ref="#places/3328"
                            key="#Spolia #Confinia #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Mention #Walls"
                            >Massaciucculi</placeName>, pertinentes ipsius ecclesie Sancti Prosperi,
                        qui una ex ipse petia <rs key="#Confinia">est tenentes uno caput</rs> cum
                        uno lato in <rs key="#Roads">via publica</rs>, alio capo in <placeName><rs
                                key="#Spolia #Walls">muro, que dicitur Antiquo</rs></placeName>, et
                        alio lato tenet in <rs key="#Rivers">rivo</rs>; et illa alia petia vocitatur
                            <placeName>ad Fenile</placeName>, est tenentes uno caput in via publica,
                        alio caput tenet in <rs key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos">padule</rs>, lato
                        uno tenet in vinea <persName>Adimari</persName>, alio lato tenet in vinea
                        monasterii Sancti Alexandri; et illa tertia petia de vinea est tenentes uno
                        caput in <rs
                            key="#Petiae #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Mention #Walls">terra
                            et muro domni regi</rs>, et alio lato tenet in via publica; et illa
                        quarta petia de vinea esse videtur in ipso loco prope eccl(esiam)
                            <orgName>Sancte Iulie</orgName>, et est tenentes uno capo in via
                        publica, alio caput tenet in vinea <persName><name ref="Georgius"
                                >Georgi</name></persName>, lato uno tenet in vinea ipsius
                        epis(copatus) vestro Sancti Martini, alio lato tenet in vinea monasterii
                            <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/3308" key="#Confinia #Monasteries"
                            >Sancti Petri, qui dicitur Bellerifonsi</orgName>; et ille quinta petia
                        de terra est tenentes uno caput in via publica, alio caput tenet in <rs
                            key="#Petiae #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Mention">terra domni
                            regi</rs>, lato uno tenet in vinea eccl(esie) Sancti Martini, et alio
                        lato tenet in terra suprascripti Georgi; has predicte quinque petiis de
                        terris et vineis (…) sunt <rs key="#Size">per mensura ad iusta perticha
                            mensuratas modiorum tres et sistariorum quinque</rs> (…) cum cesis et
                        fossis et omnibus arboribus suis. Unde et super hanc commutat(ionem)
                        secundum legem tu qui supra <persName ref="#people/214" key="#Bishops"
                            >Gherardus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> direxisti <rs
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities">missos</rs> tuos, idest
                            <persName key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities #Priests"><name
                                ref="Gundiprandus">Gudiprando</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbitero</rs>, filio <persName>qd. <name
                                ref="Adalbertus">Adalperti</name></persName>, et <persName
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities"><name ref="Teudeberto"
                                >Teuperto</name></persName> filio <persName>quondam <name
                                ref="Teofridus">Teufridi</name></persName>, et <persName
                            ref="#people/1514"
                            key="#Marquis/duke #Missus_of_other_public_authorities"
                            >Adalbertus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">dux</rs> direxit <rs
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities">misso</rs> suo, idest
                            <persName key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities"><name ref="Aufridus"
                                >Aufridi</name></persName> filio <persName>qd. <name ref="Petrus"
                                >Petri</name></persName> qui ambulaverunt (…). Pena in duplum.
                            <persName key="#Writer #Notary"><name ref="Georgius"
                            >Georgius</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> scrive due <rs key="#Commutatio"
                            >cartulas</rs>]. Actum <placeName ref="#places/4"
                            key="#Churches #Mother_churches #Monasteries #Bishops"
                        >Luca</placeName>.</ab>
                </div>
